The paper deals with designing and evaluating data structures for answering path queries on a tree, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. The paper also mentions that the problem generalizes other well-studied problems in data structures, such as orthogonal range counting and reporting in planar point sets and range median query problem in arrays. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves wavelet trees, which are commonly used in compressed data structures, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions that the path queries have applications in information retrieval, suggesting that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves designing and evaluating data structures, which could also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
